The term '''Frob''' has typically been used to refer to any small device or object (usually hand-sized) which can be manipulated, or '''''frobbed'''''.  It was adopted by the community of computer programmers ('''hackers''') which grew out of the MIT [[Tech Model Railroad Club]] (or '''TMRC''') in the 1950's.

The term can refer both to the object being frobbed (''"Hand me that frob there, willya?"'') or as an actual verb (''"Hey, frob the switch."'') indicating the manipulation of a frob.

